audit:
Verify password creation requirements conform to organization policy. Run the following command to verify the minimum password length is 14 or more characters. # grep -Pi '^\h*minlen ' /etc/security/pwquality.conf minlen = 14 Run one of the following commands to verify the required password complexity: # grep -Pi '^\h*minclass ' /etc/security/pwquality.conf minclass = 4 -OR- # grep -Pi '^\h*[duol]credit ' /etc/security/pwquality.conf dcredit = -1 ucredit = -1 lcredit = -1 ocredit = -1 Run the following commands to verify the files: /etc/pam.d/system-password and /etc/pam.d/system-auth include retry=3 on the password requisite pam_pwquality.so line: # grep -P '^\h*password\h+([^#
]+\h+)?pam_pwquality\.so\h+([^#
]+\h+)?(retry=[1- 3]) ' /etc/pam.d/system-password Example output: password    requisite     pam_pwquality.so retry=3 # grep -P '^\h*password\h+([^#
]+\h+)?pam_pwquality\.so\h+([^#
]+\h+)?(retry=[1- 3]) ' /etc/pam.d/system-auth Example output: password    requisite     pam_pwquality.so retry=3
